      "id": "d2346e162634fbf5",
      "text": "The half-dozen useful theorems are simple combinations of the axioms, usually standing in place of no more than four or five substitution steps. Volume I seeks to describe and to illustrate the visual dynamics of James algebra while emphasizing the conceptual beauty of void-based thinking and thus to motivate a completely different way of thinking about and understanding elementary arithmetic. The meta-goal is also simple: to demonstrate that symbolic mathematics is a choice rather than a necessity by providing a viable iconic alternative."
